	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65025779"><p>I'm not saying that the new ones are better. I agree that they're too new to fully trust, and even if OpenSSL had them in a workable state, I wouldn't use them for production anytime soon. But the sooner we get something viable, the sooner people can look at the algorithms with large data sets and find issues, especially implementation problems and side-channel attacks. Australia's action, even if it's risky, may well accelerate that work.</p></div>
	</div>

