			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65024291"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65024291"><p><div class="quote"><p>cert pinning</p></div><p>
Means nothing if you can compute the private key used with it.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>symmetric encryption</p></div><p>
Doesn't help here either. Both ends know the shared key, so if you can communicate at all you already have the means to get what you want from the other side.</p><p><div class="quote"><p>where signatures are not so important</p></div><p>
They are actually more important here because both sides need some way to determine the authenticity of the origins and integrity of the message. Symmetric encryption means that both sides use the same key, so the message could have originated from either end. Which may be fine depending<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65024291">

